ly of Great Britain]]\n| Cardiff\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastien Loeb]]<br />{{flagicon|Monaco}} [[Daniel Elena]]\n| [[Citro\u00ebn C4 WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2009 World Rally Championship season|2009]]\n| [[2009 Rally GB|65th Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Cardiff\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastien Loeb]]<br />{{flagicon|Monaco}} [[Daniel Elena]]\n| [[Citro\u00ebn C4 WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2010 World Rally Championship season|2010]]\n| [[2010 Rally GB|66th Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Cardiff\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastien Loeb]]<br />{{flagicon|Monaco}} [[Daniel Elena]]\n| [[Citro\u00ebn C4 WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2011 World Rally Championship season|2011]]\n| [[2011 Rally GB|67th Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Cardiff\n| {{flagicon|Finland}} [[Jari-Matti Latvala]]<br />{{flagicon|Finland}} [[Miikka Anttila]]\n| [[Ford Fiesta RS WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2012 World Rally Championship season|2012]]\n| [[2012 Rally GB|68th Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Cardiff\n| {{flagicon|Finland}} [[Jari-Matti Latvala]]<br />{{flagicon|Finland}} [[Miikka Anttila]]\n| [[Ford Fiesta RS WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2013 World Rally Championship season|2013]]\n| [[2013 Rally GB|69th Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| [[Llandudno]]\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastien Ogier]]<br />{{flagicon|France}} [[Julien Ingrassia]]\n| [[Volkswagen Polo R WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2014 World Rally Championship season|2014]]\n| [[2014 Wales Rally GB|70th Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Llandudno\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastien Ogier]]<br />{{flagicon|France}} [[Julien Ingrassia]]\n| [[Volkswagen Polo R WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2015 World Rally Championship season|2015]]\n| [[2015 Wales Rally GB|71st Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Llandudno\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastien Ogier]]<br />{{flagicon|France}} [[Julien Ingrassia]]\n| [[Volkswagen Polo R WRC]]\n|-\n! [[2016 World Rally Championship season|2016]]\n| [[2016 Wales Rally GB|72nd Wales Rally of Great Britain]]\n| Llandudno\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[S\u00e9bastie